**WOLVERINE BLEND (BPC-157 10mg/TB500 10mg)  
Instructions for Use  
**Medication Class: Injury Recovery and performance optimization.

Indications: Enhances skin health, accelerates healing and supports overall tissue regeneration. Excellent for joint and tendon repair.

**Medication Details  
**• 10/10 mg vial  
• Bacteriostatic Water 2 mL  
• Concentration: 0.05/0.05 mg per unit  
**Dosing – Daily for 10 days then re-evaluate injury**

**20 units (1mg) per day.  
_DO NOT INJECT NEAR INJURY SITE. Abdomen injection site only._** Consult your prescribing Healthcare Provider for dosage adjustments and injury evaluation.

**Storage & Handling  
**• Refrigerate after reconstitution (36°F–46°F / 2°C–8°C)  
• Do not freeze. Protect from light  
• Discard after 90 days  
  
**Missed Dose  
**• Take within 5 days if remembered  
• If more than 5 days, skip and resume weekly schedule  
• Do not double dose  
  
**Injection Technique (Summary)  
**• Inject subcutaneously into abdomen, thigh, or upper arm  
• Rotate injection sites  
• Clean site, pinch skin, inject at 90° angle  
• Dispose of syringe in sharps container  
  
This medication is compounded and provided for use only under the supervision of a licensed healthcare provider. Use only as prescribed. Individual results may vary.
